  "tips": [
    "This beautiful Pyrenean town is divided into two neighborhoods by the Ara River. It is located at the gates of the Ordesa y Monte Perdido National Park.",
    "Pelopín Peak at 2007m. Long and hard ascent until here but a long and beautiful descent to Broto.",
    "Yosa had 63 inhabitants registered in the year 1900. The last two inhabitants left the town in 1970. The town lacked a water supply and electricity and, together with its complicated access (it never had a road), these were the most important causes for its abandonment. They didn't have a doctor either, when it was necessary they had to go look for one in Broto. The priest was carried on the back of a male every Sunday to Yosa, to say mass.\n\nhttp://www.despobladosenhuesca.com/search/label/YOSA%20DE%20BROTO\n\nhttps://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yosa"
  ],
